## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design governance for large microservice ecosystems, including contract testing, versioning, auditability, and risk management under regulatory pressure.

## Key Concepts
- Contract-first API design and governance
- Versioning strategy and backward compatibility
- Contract testing integration (Pact) in CI
- Rollout strategies with canaries/flags and rollback criteria
- Immutable auditing and regulatory compliance

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pact contract test example (Node.js)
const { Pact } = require('@pact-foundation/pact');
const provider = new Pact({
  consumer: 'UserService',
  provider: 'OrderService',
  port: 1234,
  log: './pact.log',
  dir: './pacts'
});

provider.setup().then(() => {
  provider.addInteraction({
    state: 'user exists',
    uponReceiving: 'a request for user details',
    withRequest: {
      method: 'GET',
      path: '/users/123'
    },
    willRespondWith: {
      status: 200,
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: { id: 123, name: 'John Doe' }
    }
  });

  // Test consumer interaction against contract
  return axios.get('http://localhost:1234/users/123');
}).then(() => {
  provider.verify();
}).finally(() => {
  provider.finalize();
});
```

